juniRadiusDisconnectMIB.name: juniRadiusDisconnectMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module, derived from IETF Internet Drafts of RADIUS Disconnect.

juniRadiusDisconnectMIB.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886-3146 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@Juniper.net
juniRadiusDisconnectMIB.description: The RADIUS Disconnect MIB for the Juniper Networks enterprise.

juniRadiusDisconnectInvalidClientAddress.name: juniRadiusDisconnectInvalidClientAddresses
juniRadiusDisconnectInvalidClientAddress.description: The number of RADIUS disconnect packets received from unknown addresses.

juniRadiusDisconnectClientTable.name: juniRadiusDisconnectClientTable
juniRadiusDisconnectClientTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the RADIUS authentication servers with which the disconnect shares a secret.

juniRadiusDisconnectClientEntry.name: juniRadiusDisconnectClientEntry
juniRadiusDisconnectClientEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a RADIUS disconnect client with which the server shares a secret.

juniRadiusDisconnectClientAddress.name: juniRadiusDisconnectClientAddress
juniRadiusDisconnectClientAddress.description: The IP address of the RADIUS client referred to in this table entry. A value of 0.0.0.0 indicates this entry is not in use.

juniRadiusDisconnectClientPortNumber.name: juniRadiusDisconnectClientPortNumber
juniRadiusDisconnectClientPortNumber.description: The UDP port the server is listening on to recieve disconnect requests from this client.

juniRadiusDisconnectRequests.name: juniRadiusDisconnectRequests
juniRadiusDisconnectRequests.description: The number of RADIUS Disconnect packets received from this client.

juniRadiusDisconnectAccepts.name: juniRadiusDisconnectAccepts
juniRadiusDisconnectAccepts.description: The number of RADIUS Disconnects that were succesful.

juniRadiusDisconnectRejects.name: juniRadiusDisconnectRejects
juniRadiusDisconnectRejects.description: The number of RADIUS Disconnects not successful.

juniRadiusDisconnectNoSecret.name: juniRadiusDisconnectNoSecret
juniRadiusDisconnectNoSecret.description: The number of RADIUS Disconnect requests recieved from this client while no secret is set.

juniRadiusDisconnectNoSessionIds.name: juniRadiusDisconnectNoSessionIds
juniRadiusDisconnectNoSessionIds.description: The number of RADIUS Disconnect requests recieved from this client with no session-id present.

juniRadiusDisconnectBadAuthenticators.name: juniRadiusDisconnectBadAuthenticators
juniRadiusDisconnectBadAuthenticators.description: The number of RADIUS disconnect packets containing invalid authenticators received from this client.

juniRadiusDisconnectUnknownTypes.name: juniRadiusDisconnectUnknownTypes
juniRadiusDisconnectUnknownTypes.description: The number of RADIUS packets of unknown type which were received from this client on the authentication port.

juniRadiusDisconnectPacketsDropped.name: juniRadiusDisconnectPacketsDropped
juniRadiusDisconnectPacketsDropped.description: The number of RADIUS packets of which were received from this client on the authentication port and dropped for some other reason.

juniRadiusDisconnectCfgClientTable.name: juniRadiusDisconnectCfgClientTable
juniRadiusDisconnectCfgClientTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the RADIUS disconnect clients with which the server shares a secret.

juniRadiusDisconnectCfgClientEntry.name: juniRadiusDisconnectCfgClientEntry
juniRadiusDisconnectCfgClientEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a RADIUS authentication server with which the disconnect shares a secret.

juniRadiusDisconnectCfgClientAddress.name: juniRadiusDisconnectCfgClientAddress
juniRadiusDisconnectCfgClientAddress.description: The IP address of the RADIUS disconnect client referred to in this table entry.

juniRadiusDisconnectCfgClientPortNumber.name: juniRadiusDisconnectCfgClientPortNumber
juniRadiusDisconnectCfgClientPortNumber.description: The UDP port the server is listening on to recieve disconnect requests from this client.

juniRadiusDisconnectCfgKey.name: juniRadiusDisconnectCfgKey
juniRadiusDisconnectCfgKey.description: The secret (RADIUS authenticator) used by the serevr during exchanges with this client. The default is a zero-length string, indicating no authenticator is used.

juniRadiusAuthDisconnectCompliance.name: juniRadiusAuthDisconnectCompliance
juniRadiusAuthDisconnectCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Juniper RADIUS Disconnect MIB.

juniRadiusDisconnectGroup.name: juniRadiusDisconnectGroup
juniRadiusDisconnectGroup.description: The basic collection of objects providing management of RADIUS Disconnect.
